texts.text: Please...
>Someone appears to be praying...
Hear... Me...!
>A man kneels before a homemade altar as he prays desperately...

Please, hear my voice!
I beg of you!
Please, come to me!
I beg you!
What the...?!
Light...?
>Divine light saturates the man's surroundings.
*Groan*

A voice from above...
T-This must be...
>The light subsides...
>Something or someone begins to descend.

I am Sabaoth.
A Godly spirit that was once a part of God himself.
How did a mere human such as yourself call me forth?

Y-You're...
You're really here...!
I was sure that an angel was calling to me!
So I did everything I could to call them forward.
I really wasn't expecting this to work...!
>The man is overcome with joy but suddenly loses consciousness.
>In the shadows, a different kind of light begins to emerge...

Sabaoth...
The Lord of the Armies.
That voice, and this light...
You used this human to call me forth, did you now?
Elohim? Shaddai?
Indeed.
And now, you dare appear before me?
Why did you bring me here?
Sabaoth, we wish to create a new world.
Vanitas continues to be born out of human malice.
It has destroyed countless worlds across spacetime up to this point.
Near infinite, if you will.
And this world will suffer the same fate...
Faith has escaped these humans and are bringing this world closer to its doom.
The only way to save them is through "death".
Sabaoth, these humans must be erased at once.
And this world must be inherited by those worthy of being called God's children.
With our combined might, we may yet be able to create both a new heaven and Earth.
What say you, Shaddai?
I am here to listen to what you, the Lord of the Armies, has to say.
Elohim is correct in saying that this world cannot escape Vanitas.
"The end is nigh," so to speak.
However, there exist humans who wish to avoid this fate.
The Liberators...
They are working to save humanity and this world from this malice.
They may even succeed.
Which will send this world back onto the path of righteousness and ultimately save it.
You are to see for yourself and decide...
I see...
So be it.
I am willing to play along for now, Shaddai.
I, Sabaoth, shall see to this task.
>The next day.
>The Liberators are all gathered at the Hideout.

Hello.
Another incident I take it?
Nah, I got somethin' else for you today.
Yo, we've all been busy and ain't had any time to relax, right?
That's why I'm thinkin' we should go somewhere and have some fun.
Oh, all of us?!
Honey's all for that!
But we can't all leave Tokyo at once, can we?
Yo, I got that covered. We're gonna split into two groups.
That's why I had y'all come here today.
Man, I'm so ready for a vacation!
With all expenses paid by Megakin♪
For a more active vacation, I suggest we go to an airsoft camp.
Yeah, it'd be good mental and physical training!
Also, about who's going on which group...
What are you saying, pig?
Don't tell me that you want to be in the same group as me.
Even if that does happen, I'll refuse to do anything with you.
Normally, my fans would be honored to do something like this with me...
But eating into my free time...? You're just asking to be banned from my shows.
N-No, it's not like that... I'm not trying to be some kind of leech...
Please excuse my insolence!
I am a fool for even thinking that I'd be allowed to be in your group!
As long as you get it, good.
And to show my appreciation, for my next show...
You'll only need to sell twice as many tickets as usual. Now, thank me.
Thank you, ma'am!
You two never change, huh...?
What was that four eyes?
Oh, nothing.

How about you, Newbie?
What do you wanna do?
Vacation!
Airsoft camp!
Someone gets it♪
There's nothing better than having fun on someone else's dime! Am I right?!
Yo, do I even have a choice anymore...?
Yes, it wouldn't be the same without you there.
Especially since you face makes such a good... Nevermind...
>That moment...
Yo, what was that?
Everyone, it's an emergency!
The barrier around the Hideout's been broken!
Is it the Acolytes?!
No, I don't believe so...
For now, please come up to the roof!
>You see a mysterious man standing on the roof.
>But his eyes seem completely hollow...
Hey, buddy, how'd you get up here...?
My time to pass judgment has come...
Huh?

Liberators...
You will now be given a trial.
Come to the top of the Ikebukuro Eclipse Tower...
Farewell...

Yo, wait up!
You just show up outta nowhere and are tryin' to leave just like that?!
Judgment? Trial? What are you talkin' about?
Who are you?
Tell us more.
Yeah, you can start by tellin' us your name.
He's the one who broke the barrier.
There's no way he's human if he can do that.
Newbie's right.
We have better things to do if you're not willing to explain.
So be it...
>The man's appearance starts to warp.
>He glows with divine light as a sublime voice begins to echo...
I am the Godly and sublime spirit, Sabaoth.
The Lord of the Armies who commands all.
Yo, another Godly spirit...!
I have been sent here on behalf of Elohim and Shaddai to pass judgment.
And Elohim told me this.
Countless worlds have perished at the hands of Vanitas.
So, it is apparently necessary to erase those who bring it about,
and let those who are worthy of being called God's children inherit this world.
Dammit, that lightbulb's still preaching this crap...?!
If you wish to stop Elohim, you must take part in this trial.
Show me your power.
I will be waiting at the top of the tower...
Hey, wait!
>Sabaoth vanishes.
>The light wanes and everything appears to return to normal.
Shit, these things just don't quit, do they?
They all came from the same God, right? This seems normal for them.
I guess there goes our vacation.
Nooo... This is so not fair!
This is all your fault, Shionyan! You jinxed us!
Huh? What was that?
Yo, anyway...
We know that Elohim wants to "erase" us now.
But what's Sabaoth's angle here?
It wants proof that we have what it takes to protect our own world.
Something doesn't seem right.
It didn't explicitly say anything about stopping Elohim.
But Elohim aims to destroy our world, so Elohim is our enemy.
So it seems like we should be working to defeat Elohim somehow...
But it didn't sound like we're supposed to fight Elohim directly...
Hmm... Nope, don't get it.
Yo, me neither.
But none of that matters if they "erase" us before we get a chance to do anythin' about it.
Right! Our goal remains unchanged and we still have a world to protect.
So let's try our hand at this "trial".
I'm getting fired up already!
Aight!
Yo, we still don't really know what they're up to, but we gotta act!
Let's show them what we're made of.
Liberators, let's roll out!
